-ee","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H4074 (מָדַי)","strongs_def":"{Madai, a country of central Asia}","kjv_def":"Mede(-s).","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Medes(5x)"},"H4077":{"id":"H4077","lemma":"מָדַי","translit":"Mâday","pron":"maw-dah'-ee","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H4075 (מָדַי)","strongs_def":"{a Madian or native of Madai}","kjv_def":"Median.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Median(1x)"},"H4078":{"id":"H4078","lemma":"מַדַּי","translit":"madday","pron":"mad-dah'-ee","derivation":"from H4100 (מָה) and H1767 (דַּי);","strongs_def":"what (is) enough, i.e. sufficiently","kjv_def":"sufficiently."},"H4079":{"id":"H4079","lemma":"מִדְיָן","translit":"midyân","pron":"mid-yawn'","derivation":"a variation for H4066 (מָדוֹן)","strongs_def":"{a contest or quarrel}","kjv_def":"brawling, contention(-ous).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"contention(7x), brawling(2x)"},"H4080":{"id":"H4080","lemma":"מִדְיָן","translit":"Midyân","pron":"mid-yawn'","derivation":"the same as H4079 (מִדְיָן);","strongs_def":"Midjan, a son of Abraham; also his country and (collectively) his descendants","kjv_def":"Midian, Midianite.","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Midian(39x), Midianite(20x)"},"H4081":{"id":"H4081","lemma":"מִדִּין","translit":"Middîyn","pron":"mid-deen'","derivation":"a variation for H4080 (מִדְיָן)","strongs_def":"{Midjan, a son of Abraham; also his country and (collectively) his descendants}","kjv_def":"Middin.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Middin(1x)"},"H4082":{"id":"H4082","lemma":"מְדִינָה","translit":"mᵉdîynâh","pron":"med-ee-naw'","derivation":"from H1777 (דִּין);","strongs_def":"properly, a judgeship, i.e. jurisdiction; by implication, a district (as ruled by a judge); generally, a region","kjv_def":"([idiom] every) province.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"province(44x)"},"H4083":{"id":"H4083","lemma":"מְדִינָה","translit":"mᵉdîynâh","pron":"med-ee-naw'","derivation":"(A